The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for pattern recognition problems, specifically for structured problems such as image, video, or voice. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel neural learning framework for handling both homogeneous and heterogeneous data, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper performs experiments on document and molecule classification problems, which could also fall under the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
